item.title: Hashing Algorithms
item.description: def. Hash Function. A function that maps data to a hash table. Data is denoted S⊂U (=Universe) Universe can be continuous or discrete Hash table T has m slots, thus T=[m] [m]:={0,…,m−1}, [m]+:={1,…,m−1} Access time is O(1) h(x) is the hash function that takes in data point x Uniform Hash Function § def.

item.title: Homogenous Function
item.description: def. Homogenous production function f(xz,xK,xN)=xλf(z,K,N) z: Productivity K: Capital N: Labor i.e. if the inputs are multiplied by x, the output is multiplied by xλ.

item.title: Huffman Text Compression Algorithm
item.description: The Huffman algorithm is the most efficient single-text compression for text. How Computers Compress Text: Huffman Coding and Huffman Trees - YouTube Proven to be most efficient for single-character compression Uses a complete binary tree to store data Is a optimization problem.
